## Agent Handoff Commands

This repo uses [`agent-handoff`](https://github.com/charis-algomo/agent-handoff) for structured handoffs between agent sessions.

```bash
agent status              # Show current state
agent handover            # Log progress (interactive)
agent handover -s "..." -d "..." -l "..." -n "..."  # Log progress (non-interactive)
agent log                 # View handover history
agent onboard <name>      # Register a new agent tool
agent ws sync             # Sync CMUX sidebar with repo state
```

Detailed handover logs are in `.agents/handovers/`.

## CMUX Integration

If running inside [CMUX](https://cmux.dev), use these commands for real-time visibility:

### Status updates (sidebar pills)
```bash
# Show what you're working on
cmux set-status "task" "Implementing auth" --icon "hammer.fill" --color "#FFB74D"

# Track progress on long operations
cmux set-progress 0.5 --label "Running test suite..."
cmux set-progress 1.0 --label "Tests passed"

# Mark completion
cmux set-status "task" "Auth complete" --icon "checkmark.circle.fill" --color "#81C784"
cmux clear-progress
```

### Logging (sidebar log panel)
```bash
cmux log --level info --source "agent" -- "Starting migration refactor"
cmux log --level success --source "agent" -- "All tests passing"
cmux log --level warning --source "agent" -- "Deprecated API found"
cmux log --level error --source "agent" -- "Build failed"
```

### Notifications (on major milestones)
```bash
cmux notify --title "Task Complete" --body "Auth system implemented and tested"
```

### Guidelines for agents
- Update `cmux set-status "task"` when starting a new logical task
- Use `cmux set-progress` during long operations (builds, large refactors)
- Use `cmux log` for significant events, not every small step
- Use `cmux notify` only for major milestones
- Always guard with `command -v cmux &>/dev/null` — skip silently if unavailable

## Playwright CLI (UI Testing)

If [Playwright CLI](https://playwright.dev/) is available, use it for browser automation and UI testing. It's ~4x more token-efficient than MCP — saves accessibility tree to disk and sends only a summary.

### Quick reference
```bash
playwright-cli open <url>               # Open a browser session
playwright-cli open <url> --headed      # Visible browser window
playwright-cli snapshot                  # Get accessibility tree snapshot
playwright-cli fill "input#email" "test@example.com"  # Fill a form field
playwright-cli click "Submit"            # Click an element (use snapshot refs)
playwright-cli screenshot                # Take a screenshot
playwright-cli close                     # Close the session
```

### Named sessions (for parallel testing)
```bash
playwright-cli open https://example.com -s=session-1
playwright-cli open https://example.com -s=session-2
playwright-cli snapshot -s=session-1     # Snapshot a specific session
```

### Agent CLI wrappers
```bash
